SIMPLE: chirk
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chirk
<hw>Chirk</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Chirp</er>,
also <er>Creak</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To shriek; to gnash; to
utter harsh or shrill cries.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All full of <qex>chirkyng</qex> was that sorry place.</q>
<rj><qau>Cheucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To chirp like a bird.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chirk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Chirk
<hw>Chirk</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cheer; to enliven; <as>as, to
<ex>chirk</ex> one up</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq. New Eng. ]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chirk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Chirk
<hw>Chirk</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Chirk</er>, <pos>v.
i.</pos>]</ety> <def>Lively; cheerful; in good spirits.</def>
<mark>[Colloq. New Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chirm</ent>⟦br⟧
